aws::graph::propositions: # Piper PA-11 Aircraft Accident Information
The aircraft experienced abnormal runway contact during landing.
The aircraft experienced loss of control on ground during landing roll.
The aircraft experienced an aborted landing after touchdown.
The pilot held a Private certificate.
The pilot was 62 years old.
The pilot was male.
The pilot had a Single-engine land airplane rating.
The pilot had no Other Aircraft Ratings.
The pilot had an Instrument Rating for Airplane.
The pilot had no Instructor Ratings.
The pilot held a Class 3 Medical Certification with waivers/limitations.
The pilot's last Federal Aviation Administration Medical Examination was on February 3, 2012.
The pilot's last Flight Review or Equivalent was on February 4, 2012.
The pilot had 746 hours of total flight time in all aircraft.
The pilot had 11 hours of total flight time in this make and model.
No second pilot was present during the accident.
No toxicology was performed on the pilot.
The aircraft was a Piper PA-11.
The aircraft registration was N4844M.
The aircraft category was Airplane.
The aircraft had an Airworthiness Certificate classified as Normal.
The aircraft serial number was 11-361.
The aircraft had a tailwheel landing gear type.
The aircraft had 2 seats.
The aircraft's last inspection was an Annual inspection on August 1, 2011.
The aircraft's certified maximum gross weight was 1220 pounds.
The aircraft had 1 Reciprocating engine.
The aircraft's airframe total time was 3785 hours as of the last inspection.
The aircraft's engine manufacturer was Continental Motor.
The aircraft's engine model/series was C90 Series.
The aircraft's engine was rated at 95 Horsepower.
The aircraft had an Emergency Locator Transmitter installed and activated, but it did not aid in locating the accident.
The registered owner of the aircraft was Jeffrey H. Gaier.
The operator of the aircraft was Steven Humphrey.
The operator held no Operating Certificates.
